<h2>Open Source Projects</h2>
<ul>
<li>currently working on Debian port to AMD64 architecture (AMD Opteron chip); see http://www.jukie.net/~bart/debian/amd64/.</li>
<li>previously involved in redesign efforts of KLIPS (kernel part of the IPSec implementation for Linux); my involvement lies in the development of a kernel-space crypto library: http://www.jukie.net/~bart/linux-ipsec.</li>
<li>developed an elf signing utility which uses the GnuPG engine for digitally signing elf executables: http://elfsign.sourceforge.net.</li>
